Package settings.types

Class Setting<T>

java.lang.Object
settings.types.Setting<T>
Type Parameters:
T - Type of value of the setting
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
BooleanSetting, FileSetting, IntSetting, ListSetting, MapSetting, SetSetting, StringSetting
public abstract class Setting<T> extends Object implements Serializable
An abstract method that provides method dictations, parameters, and methods a Setting class should have. This class provides the following implementations:
  • Setting value, of type T, including methods to get and set the value
  • Setting name. Initialized in constructors, and represents the official name for the setting.
  • Categories the setting falls under, including methods to get the categories, as well as to check if the setting falls under any category in a provided set.
Author:
Thomas Kwashnak
